changes in nl3-files when running script_nl3

note: short files are without add. H/He files,
       long files include add. H/He files (currently, 16 lines more)
       
*info* file is always ascii       

mkatom ...

creates nl3info, nl3i, nl3a, nl3g  in fw_data/Line-List-Bin-Source
        short, binary
	
nl3info compared with wmbasic_data/nl3info  short, should be identical

then

nl3 files moved to fw_data_new   fw_data/Line-List-Bin-Source empty, 

fw_data_new now contains nl3info, nl3i, nl3a, nl3g short, binary


switch to dir_atomnl2_meta

meta_2.0.eo uses nl3info, nl3i, nl3a, nl3g from fpath2 = fw_data_new
        defined in metacom: short, binary
	
writes to (locally, i.e. dir_atomnl2_meta
        nl3info_all, nl3i_all_ascii, nl3a_all_ascii, nl3g_all_ascii
        short, ascii. 
	At this point, nl3info in fw_user_data and nl3info_all in
        dir_atomnl2_meta should be equal (except format)
	
switch to make_...  (=main) directory
       
conv_ascii_add_HHelines reads 
       nl3i_all_ascii, nl3a_all_ascii, nl3g_all_ascii from dir_atomnl2_meta
       short, ascii
       and fw_data_new: nl3info (short)
       
and creates       
       nl3info_all, nl3i_all, nl3a_all, nl3g_all in fw_data_new
       long, binary 
       
at this point, we have the following files
      
dir_atomnl2_meta: nl3i_all_ascii, nl3a_all_ascii, nl3g_all_ascii 
                  short, ascii
                  nl3info_all short_ascii
		  
fw_data_new: nl3info, nl3i, nl3a, nl3g (short, binary)
             nl3info_all, nl3i_all, nl3a_all, nl3g_all (long, binary)
	     
at this point, nl3info (created with mkatom) should be short
               and identical to nl3info_all in dir_atomnl2_meta
	       nl3info_all in fw_user should be different (long)
	       
finally, all nl3? files in fw_data_new deleted. 

